 One man was killed and 22 others injured when a truck overturned on the R614 outside of Wartburg, KwaZulu-Natal. The accident occurred on Wednesday morning. ER24 and other emergency services arrived on the scene around 07:30 to find a truck lying on its roof on the side of the road. Russel Meiring, communications officer for ER24, said in a statement that "it is believed that the driver lost control of the vehicle, causing it to roll". According to Meiring, the passengers, who had been on the back of the truck, were found scattered around the accident scene. Emergency personnel assessed the patients and found that one man had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. He was subsequently declared dead on the scene.       https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/1-person-dead-22-inj 